The Scenario: A surveyor is tasked with carving out exactly a 0.11 Acre (0.046 Ha) plot (Plot A) from a parent
parcel.
The Field Data: The surveyor shoots the outer boundary with an RTK rover, establishing the original
perimeter pegs: P1, P2, P4, and P5.

The Manual Bottleneck:
1. The Iterative Cut: The surveyor has to manually draw a dividing line between the top and bottom
boundaries, nudging it left and right in AutoCAD. They must continually recalculate the area until the
enclosed polygon exactly hits 460 sqm (0.046 Ha).
2. The Transcription Trap: This manual cut creates two new derived vertices (P3 and P6). The
surveyor must read the X/Y coordinates for P6 (9988950.65) from the CAD software and type them
manually into the text table on the mutation form. A single typo here results in Ministry of Lands
rejection.

The VipimoAI Automation (Phase A Engine):
1. The Slide Line Solver: VipimoAI does not guess. The algorithm anchors to the western boundary
vector and mathematically "slides" a cut-line eastwards. The binary search function calculates the area
at machine speed, perfectly locking in the 0.046 Ha target and establishing P3 and P6 instantly.
2. Zero-Transcription Error: The `generateCoordinateSchedule()` function programmatically extracts
the exact X/Y values from the generated spatial geometry and renders the Northings/Eastings table
directly onto the PDF.

Case Study 2: Multi-Target Succession & Frontage Optimization

